###########################################################################
#  crossref_pageof - a tiny @Report with both forward and backward
#  cross references via @PageOf / @NumberOf / @TitleOf.  Exercises the
#  multi-pass cross-reference resolution machinery: on the first pass
#  the references render blank, on the second they pick up the right
#  page and section numbers from the .li database.
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { report }

@Report
    @Title { Cross-reference Smoke Test }
    @Author { Tester }
    @InitialLanguage { English }
//

@Section
    @Title { Introduction }
    @Tag { intro }
@Begin
@PP
This document exists to exercise Lout's forward and backward reference
machinery.  In Section @NumberOf { conclusions } (page
@PageOf { conclusions }) we will revisit the topic, and the
section there is called "@TitleOf { conclusions }".  The last page of
this document is page @PageOf { last.page }.
@End @Section

@Section
    @Title { Conclusions }
    @Tag { conclusions }
@Begin
@PP
As foreshadowed in Section @NumberOf { intro } (page
@PageOf { intro }), we wrap things up here.  The intro section was
called "@TitleOf { intro }".
@End @Section
